# HealthAI Assistant — API Tests
# Extension: REST Client (Huachao Mao) — free, works in VS Code
# Usage: click "Send Request" above any request block
#
# SETUP: fill in your values in the @variables below

@parse_url = https://parseapi.back4app.com
@base_url = http://localhost:3000
@app_id = YOUR_BACK4APP_APP_ID
@js_key = YOUR_BACK4APP_JS_KEY

# After running "Login User", copy sessionToken from the response
# and paste it here:
@session_token = PASTE_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### AUTH
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### TC-AUTH-01: Register User (expect 201)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/users
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "pass123",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "allergies": [],
  "conditions": [],
  "medications": []
}

###

### TC-AUTH-02: Register with duplicate username (expect 400, code 202)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/users
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "pass123",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

###

### TC-AUTH-04: Login with valid credentials (expect 200 + sessionToken)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/login
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "pass123"
}

###

### TC-AUTH-05: Login with wrong password (expect 404, code 101)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/login
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### TC-AUTH-06: Login with non-existent user (expect 404, code 101)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/login
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "doesnotexist",
  "password": "pass123"
}

###


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### HEALTH LOGS
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### TC-LOG-01: Create health log (authenticated) (expect 201)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/classes/HealthLog
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symptoms": "headache and fatigue",
  "severity": "medium",
  "notes": "Started after lunch",
  "vitals": {
    "heartRate": 82,
    "bloodPressure": "120/80",
    "temperature": 99.1
  }
}

###

### TC-LOG-02: Create health log (unauthenticated) (expect 403)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/classes/HealthLog
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symptoms": "headache",
  "severity": "low"
}

###

### TC-LOG-03: Get health logs (authenticated) (expect 200 with results array)
GET {{parse_url}}/1/classes/HealthLog?order=-createdAt&limit=50
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}

###

### TC-LOG-05: Delete health log (replace OBJECT_ID with id from TC-LOG-01)
DELETE {{parse_url}}/1/classes/HealthLog/REPLACE_WITH_OBJECT_ID
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}

###


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### CONVERSATIONS
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### TC-CONV-01: Save conversation (expect 201)
POST {{parse_url}}/1/classes/Conversation
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Headache symptoms",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "I have a headache" },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "How long have you had it?" }
  ],
  "lastMessage": "How long have you had it?"
}

###

### TC-CONV-02: Get conversations (expect 200 with results array)
GET {{parse_url}}/1/classes/Conversation?order=-createdAt&limit=20
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}

###

### TC-CONV-03: Delete conversation (replace OBJECT_ID with id from TC-CONV-01)
DELETE {{parse_url}}/1/classes/Conversation/REPLACE_WITH_OBJECT_ID
X-Parse-Application-Id: {{app_id}}
X-Parse-Javascript-Key: {{js_key}}
X-Parse-Session-Token: {{session_token}}

###


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### AI ROUTES (run `npm run dev` first)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### TC-CHAT-01: Valid chat message (expect 200 streaming text)
POST {{base_url}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "I have a mild headache" }
  ],
  "userProfile": {
    "allergies": ["penicillin"],
    "conditions": ["asthma"],
    "medications": ["inhaler"],
    "age": 28,
    "bloodType": "O+"
  }
}

###

### TC-CHAT-03: Emergency keyword (expect 200, response starts with [EMERGENCY])
POST {{base_url}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "I have chest pain and can't breathe" }
  ]
}

###

### TC-CHAT-04: Empty messages array (expect 400)
POST {{base_url}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": []
}

###

### TC-INSIGHTS-01: Health insights with logs (expect 200 with insights text)
POST {{base_url}}/api/health-insights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "logs": [
    {
      "symptoms": "headache and fatigue",
      "severity": "medium",
      "notes": "After lunch",
      "createdAt": "2026-06-25T10:00:00.000Z",
      "vitals": { "heartRate": 82, "temperature": 99.1 }
    },
    {
      "symptoms": "mild back pain",
      "severity": "low",
      "notes": "",
      "createdAt": "2026-06-24T08:00:00.000Z",
      "vitals": {}
    }
  ],
  "profile": {
    "age": 28,
    "bloodType": "O+",
    "allergies": [],
    "conditions": [],
    "medications": []
  }
}

###

### TC-INSIGHTS-02: Empty logs (expect 200 with "no logs" message)
POST {{base_url}}/api/health-insights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "logs": [],
  "profile": null
}

###

### TC-INSIGHTS-03: Missing logs field (expect 400)
POST {{base_url}}/api/health-insights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "profile": {}
}
